4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, licensed midwives are
6 required to order certain newborn screening tests for
7 diseases pursuant to the Newborn Screening Program
8 under the Alabama Department of Public Health.
9 This bill would authorize licensed midwives to
10 administer those screening tests in accordance with the
11 program.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 Relating to midwifery; to amend Section 34-19-16, Code
19 of Alabama 1975, to authorize licensed midwives to administer
20 screening for certain diseases in newborns pursuant to the
21 Newborn Screening Program.
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
23 Section 1. Section 34-19-16, Code of Alabama 1975, is
24 amended to read as follows:
25 "§34-19-16
26 (a) A licensed midwife may provide midwifery care in
27 the setting of the client's choice, except a hospital.
28 (b) A licensed midwife shall ensure that the client has
