29 signed a midwife disclosure form provided by the board
30 indicating receipt of a written statement that includes all of
31 the following information:
32 (1) A description of the licensed midwife's education,
33 training, and experience in midwifery.
34 (2) Antepartum, intrapartum, and postpartum conditions
35 requiring medical referral, transfer of care, and transport to
36 a hospital.
37 (3) A plan for medical referral, transfer of care, and
38 transport of the client or newborn or both when indicated by
39 specific antepartum, intrapartum, or postpartum conditions.
40 (4) Instructions for filing a complaint against a
41 licensed midwife.
42 (5) A statement that the licensed midwife must comply
43 with the federal Health Insurance Portability and
44 Accountability Act.
45 (6) The status of a licensed midwife's professional
46 liability insurance coverage.
47 (7) References to current evidence regarding the safety
48 of midwifery care in out-of-hospital settings, including a
49 copy of the most recent statement by the American Congress of
50 Obstetricians and Gynecologists on home birth.
51 (c) A licensed midwife shall ensure that the client has
52 signed an informed consent form provided by the board.
53 (d) For screening purposes only, a licensed midwife may
54 order routine antepartum and postpartum laboratory analyses to
55 be performed by a licensed laboratory.
56 (e) After a client has secured the services of a
