57 licensed midwife, the licensed midwife shall document an
58 emergency care plan on a form provided by the board.
59 (f) A licensed midwife shall determine the progress of
60 labor and, when birth is imminent, shall be available until
61 delivery is accomplished.
62 (g) A licensed midwife shall remain with the client
63 during the postpartal period until the conditions of the
64 client and newborn are stabilized.
65 (h) A licensed midwife shall instruct the client
66 regarding the requirements of the administration of eye
67 ointment ordered by the Alabama Department of Public Health
68 pursuant to Section 22-20-2.
69 (i) A licensed midwife shall instruct the client
70 regarding the requirements of administration of newborn health
71 screening ordered by the Alabama Department of Public Health
72 pursuant to Section 22-20-3.
73 (j) A licensed midwife shall file a birth certificate
74 for each birth in accordance with the requirements of Section
75 22-9A-7.
76 (k) A licensed midwife shall collect clinical data
77 under the Midwives Alliance of North America Statistics
78 Project for each client who initiates care and shall submit a
79 copy of the clinical data collected for each consenting client
80 to the board upon request.
81 (l) A licensed midwife shall report to the Alabama
82 Department of Public Health pursuant to Chapter 11A, of Title
83 22, and any other law that requires hospitals or physicians to
84 report to the Alabama Department of Public Health.
